import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['speed'], bins=20, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['speed'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['speed'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['speed'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['speed'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Wind Speed')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of wind speed?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    plt.xlabel('Wind Direction')
    plt.ylabel('Wind Speed')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between wind speed and direction?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.style.use('ggplot')
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax = data['dirCat'].value_counts().sort_index().plot(kind='bar', color='blue', edgecolor='black', linewidth=0.5)
    ax.set_xlabel('Wind Direction Categories')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of wind direction categories?')
    for i in ax.patches:
        ax.text(i.get_x() + 0.2, i.get_height() + 1, str(i.get_height()), fontsize=8, color='black')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 8))
    heatmap, xedges, yedges = np.histogram2d(data['longitude'], data['latitude'], bins=50)
    extent = [xedges[0], xedges[-1], yedges[0], yedges[-1]]
    plt.imshow(heatmap.T, extent=extent, origin='lower', cmap='coolwarm')
    plt.colorbar()
    plt.xlabel('Longitude')
    plt.ylabel('Latitude')
    plt.title('What is the spatial distribution of wind vectors?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
